i think my mouse is sick hi i have two mice ones name is joeshine she is a girl and latey i have noticed her to not be so social and her poop is very runny and shes not eating much or drinking much do i need to take the other out or what please help me decide what is wrong hi it sounds like your mouse is very sick i would get her to the vet asap if this is not possible then i don't think there is much more you can do i don't think it would be worth taking your other mouse out as chances are shes already got it as well but it's always worth a try if you have a local pet store near you i would go there and ask if they have any medications for mice that seem suitable for your mouses symptoms good luck to you and your mice Guinea pig Garfield Fancy rat House Mouse Mouse Fasting Social rule Rat Decompression sickness Hamster The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy Primary and Secondary Phases Sleeping sickness Cat Pet store Brown Rat Attention-deficit hyperactivity disorder Ferret Common cold Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma FLCL Apple Computer Baldrick Domestic rabbit Taboo food and drink Ron Weasley Pitaten Disease Vomiting Sin City Timon and Pumbaa Jackass: The Movie Binary classification Oh My Goddess! The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy (film) Password The Smoking Room The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Shit Colorectal cancer Scrooge McDuck Minnie Mouse The Secret of NIMH David Lee Roth Dumbo Spanish flu Ghostwriter (television series) Internet phenomenon Pet Sounds Calvin and Hobbes Practices of Jehovah's Witnesses Neighbours Urinary incontinence Prisoner (TV series) Elephant Tuberculosis Mickey Mouse Three Stooges The Adventures of Pete & Pete Menstrual cycle Teen Girl Squad Shaggy dog story Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Saki Insulin Asthma Stuttering Commodore International Friends Rabies Cocaine Parkinson's disease Gladstone Gander The Beach Boys Radiation poisoning Aladdin (1992 film) Health insurance Combat stress reaction Characters in the Smurfs Antidepressant Schizophr